National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy and other officials in Kyiv to express the United States' unwavering support for Ukraine's defense of its sovereignty and territorial integrity. Sullivan announced a new security assistance package worth $400 million, which includes refurbished T-72 tanks, unmanned aerial vehicles, and the refurbishment of HAWK surface-to-air missiles for eventual transfer to Ukraine. He also confirmed that the US will continue to provide economic and humanitarian aid and work with partners to hold Russia accountable for its aggressive actions.